The benefits of the operation will surpass its costs due to the fact that the state will receive 100 percent of associated profits compared to 60 percent in corporate income tax that was going to be paid by Chevron. In this context, fiscal oil revenues will be higher than originally forecasted over the remainder of the consortium’s operations. However, while the acquisition’s financing will lead to some reduction in fiscal oil revenues during its repayment period, those shortfalls will be relatively limited and offset soon thereafter. Furthermore, thanks to the $\cup5\$100$ million tax settlement with Chevron, the net   
budgetary impact is slightly positive for 2014.

